gomodel:SYNGO_4914  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Figure 2: muscarinic M1 receptor (M1R, gene CHRM1) DAB immunolabeling in the primate dorsolateral prefrontal cortex showed localization at dendritic spines, putative GABAergic postsynapses, dendrites and astrocytes (Fig. S2). The omission of the primary antibody or substitution with non-immune serum abolished all reactivity.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Brain tissue from four adult Rhesus macaques (10-22 y.o., female)\nCHRM1 antibody: Sigma Aldrich Cat # M9808; RRID:AB_260731" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
